EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT STUDY
OF MOTOR VEHICLE NON-EXHAUST PARTICLE EMISSIONS
***
1 This act would require the department of transportation, in consultation with the
2 department of environmental management, to conduct an environmental impact study of motor
3 vehicle non-exhaust particle emissions. It also would allow the departments to collaborate with an
4 academic research institute and direct the departments to make specific recommendations to the
5 general assembly to reduce the environmental impact of tire particle emissions. Their report would
6 be completed no later than January 1, 2026.
7 This act would take effect upon passage.
